        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01M5.636 5.636L18.364 18.364M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" /></svg>
        Not on the {year} calendar
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-gradient-accent">
        Hyrox {explainerCityHeadline} {year}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Hyrox {explainer.localCity ?? explainer.city} {year} is not on the official Hyrox calendar. Below: closest substitute races, training options, and where to follow if Hyrox returns to {explainer.city}.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose md:prose-lg max-w-none mb-10">
      {explainer.intro.map((p) => <p>{p}</p>)}
    </section>

    {explainerSubstituteEvents.length > 0 && (
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-text-heading mb-2">Closest Hyrox races to {explainer.city} in {year}</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted mb-6 max-w-3xl">Race the closest Hyrox on the {year} calendar instead. Open any city for full event details, venue, and registration.</p>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          {explainerSubstituteEvents.map(({ sub, event: subEvent }) => (
            <a
              href={`/events/${subEvent.year}/${subEvent.slug}/`}
              class="block bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-2xl p-5 hover:border-accent/40 hover:bg-bg-card-hover transition-all no-underline"
            >
              <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-accent mb-1">{subEvent.country}</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-black text-text-heading mb-1">Hyrox {subEvent.city} {subEvent.year}</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-2">{formatEventDate(subEvent.startDate, subEvent.endDate)} · {subEvent.venue}</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">{sub.note}</div>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    {explainer.evergreenCitySlug && (
      <section class="mb-12 bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-2xl p-6">
        <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-accent mb-2">Hyrox in {explainer.city}</div>
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black text-text-heading mb-3">Evergreen guide to Hyrox {explainer.city}</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The local training-club ecosystem, race history, and venue notes don't change just because the calendar moves. Use the evergreen city guide to find Hyrox-affiliated training clubs in {explainer.city} and follow when the race returns.
        </p>
        <a href={`/hyrox/${explainer.evergreenCitySlug}/`} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-white font-bold text-sm rounded-xl px-5 py-2.5 hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity no-underline">
          Open the Hyrox {explainer.city} guide →
        </a>
      </section>
    )}

    <section class="prose md:prose-lg max-w-none mb-10">
      <h2>How to train for Hyrox without a home race</h2>
      <p>
        If your home city isn't on the calendar, the build-up looks the same as any other Hyrox cycle: 8 to 16 weeks of running, sled work, and high-rep wall balls. The only adjustment is that race weekend includes travel. Most athletes plan one final long-haul training session 10-14 days out, then taper and travel.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the <a href="/calculator/">Hyrox time calculator</a> to set a realistic finish target.</li>
        <li>Browse <a href="/training-plans/">structured training plans</a> by goal time and experience level.</li>
        <li>Check the <a href={`/gyms/${explainer.evergreenCitySlug ?? explainer.city.toLowerCase()}/`}>{explainer.city} gym directory</a> for local Hyrox-affiliated training clubs.</li>
        <li>Read the <a href="/blog/hyrox-race-week-protocol/">race-week taper protocol</a> for the final 7 days before any away race.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Other Hyrox races in {year}</h2>
      <p>
        See the full <a href={`/events/${year}/`}>Hyrox {year} calendar</a> for every race city, venue, and date. The calendar covers all confirmed stops globally.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
)}
